news.title: Brazil eases financing for low-income home buyers
news.para: The measures, which will take effect in about 60 days, are aimed at increasing access to affordable housing and boosting economic growth with more support for civil construction.

news.title: Royalty hike on marble, granite upsets tiles industry
news.para: As per the new order, royalty for marble slabs and tiles increased to Rs 500 from Rs 430 per tonne. Royalty on granite blocks having more than 70 cm dimension went up from Rs 215 to Rs 300 and from sizes less than 70 cm, the rate will be Rs 150 instead of Rs 90 per tonne.

news.title: SBI announces various offers for home loan borrowers
news.para: With the introduction of the new offer, a borrower can now avail home loan for any amount at a rate as low as 6.70 per cent, the bank said in a release.

news.title: Vadodara civic body to get Rs 167 crore towards land for bullet train project
news.para: NHSRCL is set to acquire land from VMC on the alignment for the bullet train. The alignment of the train traverses through the city from Chhani on one end and to Maneja on the other.

news.title: No homestay permitted in Nilgiris district: Madras HC
news.para: ​​Till a plan is put in place upon appropriate studies being conducted and a viable scientific report being obtained, no further permission for homestays in the Nilgiris should be granted, the court ruled.

news.title: Hyderabad: What ban? Illegal structures overrun all GO 111 villages
news.para: This despite a ruling by the National Green Tribunal (NGT) staying all activity in this no-construction belt spread over 84 villages which fall in the catchment area of two of Hyderabad’s biggest fresh water lakes - Osmansagar and Himayatsagar.

news.title: Researchers develop low-carbon bricks using construction waste
news.para: These low-carbon (low-C) bricks, as the team calls it, do not require high-temperature firing, and avoid the use of high-energy materials such as Portland cement.

news.title: Gurugram: Special teams to survey pending infrastructure in 11 colonies
news.para: MCG officials said while eight of these colonies — Mayfield Garden, Malibu Towne, Sushant Lok-2 and 3, Greenwood City, Rosewood City, Vipul World and Uppal Housing — have given their consent for takeover by the corporation, they haven’t received consent from Ardee City and DLF-4 and 5.

news.title: Will complete first phase housing project by next Ugadi: Andhra Pradesh minister
news.para: Andhra Pradesh housing minister Cherukuvada Sri Rangantha Raju said that the government itself is taking up the construction of nearly 9508 housing units in the colony following the requests of the beneficiaries.

news.title: Over 47,500 houses in Delhi meant for slum-dwellers to be used under ARHCs scheme
news.para: The Delhi PWD minister Satyendar Jain shared the details during a press conference here, and in response to a question said that new housing facilities will have to be built now for those residing in slums and JJ colonies.

news.title: Sunteck Realty plans JDA to develop 10 million sq ft in Mumbai
news.para: The project will see a potential development of about 10 million sq ft and is expected to generate around Rs 9,000 crore over the next 7-8 years, according to the company.

news.title: Expect upside in housing sector in short, medium and long term: Keki Mistry
news.para: “In the short term, NPLs can go up but that’s it. To my mind, with every passing month post the second wave, we have seen collections getting better. The collection number for individuals was 98% when we last reviewed.”

news.title: NITI Aayog & Maharashtra CM discuss metro, Dharavi redevelopment, other issues
news.para: NITI Aayog vice-chairman Dr Rajiv Kumar, CEO Amitabh Kant and its member Ramesh Chand held talks with Thackeray, an official statement issued by the Chief Minister's Office (CMO) said.

news.title: At next board meet, Noida authority may slash property transfer charges
news.para: Though officials say they have been asked to get ready to hold the meeting next week, they are yet to get the final go-ahead from Authority chairman Sanjeev Mittal.

news.title: Blackstone sells 5.7 crore units in Embassy Office Parks REIT for over Rs 2,000 crore
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT is the country's first real estate investment trust (REIT), sponsored by realty firm Embassy group and Blackstone.
